I have a vector $\mathbf{a}=(a_1,a_2,a_3)$, where $a_1,a_2,a_3$ are real numbers. I now want to write that $\mathbf{a}$ is a vector in $\mathbb{R}^3$ and that $a_1,a_2,a_3$ are real numbers. What is the proper notation for this? Is it correct to write
